<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Trallos Coldhart</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-06 15:33:15</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This guy's a great camp for anyone levels 32-37 or so.  You sit in this little room with 6 people (you need a full group, it can be dangerous) and one person pulls everything from the Bubble (where the AoF spawns) to the sewers behind the little room.  You can gain about a bubble every 1-2 hours this way.  The avatar of fear is funny because he also spawns as a Place Holder fairly often.  Sometimes he spawns a lot, sometimes a not at all.  One night I camped him and he didn't spawn for 6 hours.  Another night, he spawned 4 times in a row (Bladed Thulian Claws for everyone!).  He is NOT to be taken lightly, of course.  If your group isn't prepared for him he can really f it up; he can (double) hit for 90 and each hit is only a second or two apart.  Make sure you have someone with evacuate memorized (saved my life more then once).  He can't see invisible things, so if you need to get to the room and he's up dont be afraid.  About the loot, I've never killed him without him having thulian claws.  I've never killed him with a Ravenscale BP (although I do know it drops).  I've killed this guy about 8 times and was killed by him twice (I think).  In the heat of combat, I don't even remember if he casted spells.  I don't think he did.  If you want a screenshot just look at cazic thule and then imagine him being about as tall as a barbarian.  That's the Avatar of Fear.<BR>
<BR>
Suggested Avatar of Fear group:<BR>
Warrior (required)<BR>
     Don't go down there without a tank because the AoF can take down most classes other then warrior in just a few hits.<BR>
Healer (REQUIRED)<BR>
     Not much to be said.<BR>
Enchanter<BR>
     While not required, will make life MUCH safer.  Clarity helps healers and nukers get mana faster and crowd control will save the group's life from big pulls.<BR>
Evacuator<BR>
     This can be a druid, who will double as a healer/buffer, or a wizard, who will double as a nuker.  Don't underestimate the value of a wizard down here.  They can really fuck shit up with their nukes.<BR>
2 spots of your choice<BR>
     In the past I seem to have had a lot of twinked rogues in my group.  Dunno why but hey, it killed the monster faster.  Another warrior or hybrid tank is nice as an extra, of course.  And a healer is great to.  Therefore, my suggested is a tank and a healer for the extras.  It's almost safe if you get them.<BR>
<BR>
There ya go, one of the best places to get exp/loot for mid 30's in the game (in my opinion).  If you need someone to show you to the room, ask someone in Cazic ( there is usually a group there anyways).<BR>
<BR>
~Trallos Coldhart<BR>
~Warrior of the 35th Circle<BR>
~Ministers of Death<BR>
~Wolf of the North<BR>
<BR>
p.s.  Hey Aeain, you remember the time I was going to your AoF group and then I saw the AoF following you up the halls?  still sticks out in my mind lol</font></td></tr></table>
